.TH GIT\-ISSUE\-IMPORT 1 "2026-02-07" "git-issue 1.0.0" "Git Issue Manual"
.SH NAME
git\-issue\-import \- import issues from an external provider
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git issue import
.IR github: <owner> / <repo>
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Import issues from an external issue tracker into the local Git
repository as
.B git\-issue
refs.
.PP
Currently supported providers:
.TP
.BI github: <owner> / <repo>
GitHub Issues via the GitHub CLI
.RB ( gh ).
.PP
Already-imported issues (identified by their
.B Provider\-ID:
trailer) are skipped.
Comments are imported as child commits, and closed issues receive a
state-change commit.
Original authors and timestamps are preserved.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-state " " <state>
Filter issues to import:
.BR open " (default), " closed ", " all .
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be imported without making changes.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage information.
.SH PREREQUISITES
.IP \(bu 2
.BR gh (1)
(GitHub CLI), authenticated via
.BR "gh auth login" .
.IP \(bu 2
.BR jq (1)
for JSON processing.
.SH EXAMPLES
Import open issues:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue import github:owner/repo
.fi
.RE
.PP
Preview what would be imported:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue import github:owner/repo --state all --dry-run
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git\-issue (1),
.BR git\-issue\-export (1),
.BR git\-issue\-sync (1),
.BR gh (1)
